summary: Arya x Gendry Week, Day 1: Eye Contact  “Would you shut up!” Arya whisper-hissed at Sansa, who merely kept up that mocking...
body:
Arya x Gendry Week, Day 1: Eye Contact


“Would you shut up!” Arya whisper-hissed at Sansa, who merely kept up that mocking smile, that menacing terrible smile. She did raise an eyebrow though, very satisfied that she was irritating her sister. Because what else were sisters good for if not for irritating? Nothing Arya was pretty sure.

“He’s just so cute. And I know you’ve always wanted a guy who could take a hit.” Arya sighed aggressively, rolling her eyes and looking away while Sansa tittered.

“Very funny.” She muttered in return, glancing back to the guy in question. Given they were in an emergency room waiting area, it was perhaps not the most surprising that he was injured but still… He looked rock solid, strong as a bull and powerful. His two friends chattered at him incessantly, and loudly too, Arya could hear them from over here. The guy though, the guy was silent. Pitch silent. That wasn’t a phrase. He was expanding her vocabulary just by looking at him. He looked away from the other two, staring off into space, probably trying not to focus on the pain.

“Just go over and talk to him!” Sansa would not leave well enough alone. Arya was not particularly interested in finding her next date in the waiting room of a hospital. That was pretty stupid.

“He has a head injury!” Arya protested, and she could feel them getting louder with each passing remark in the argument. Blood pulsed from the guy’s forehead. It was nasty. Maybe it’d leave a scar.

“So do you!” Rickon had thrown a snowball at her. It accidentally had a rock in it. He had cried about it more than she had. Still, she imagined her face was just as bloodstained. Maybe a little less. “It’s a conversation starter.” Sansa continued, and Arya could hear the simple glee in her voice, a simple enjoyment of this situation. Sansa liked this… the whole dating thing. She did it a lot. Arya was not as interested. She was pickier maybe, or maybe the ideals of romance didn’t sit right, or maybe… She just didn’t, okay? She didn’t need to explain herself to her own inner monologue. The point was Sansa was having too much fun with this, and Arya was not going to talk to him partially because to do so would mean Sansa won. And Arya was not about to let anyone win anything. Particularly not involving her and some guy. “It’s just so romantic! Both struck on the same day, matching scars, a lovely conversation where you berate his friends for being the loudest thing since a Metallica concert. And then you jump his bones…”

“Sansa!” Arya shouted, glancing at her sister for a second before going back to enjoying the view… fuck he’d turned his head. He was looking right at her. Right at her. His eyes were startling. She had imagined some baby cow brown, big and cute but no malice in them. It’d fit the farmhand body he had. But no. They were blue. Demanding blue, fierce, unrelenting blue. They were gorgeous and she could not look away. “Fuck,” Arya muttered, not breaking the eye contact. “His eyes, Sansa,”

“I win,” Her sister whispered.

“Arya!” The clerk or whatever called. Her turn for treatment. Arya pulled her eyes away, blushing like a… she didn’t know what. So much for expanding her vocabulary. She hurried away, her sister giggling and teasing as she did.

title: all i ask: chapter one — eye contact
body:
Fandoms / Pairing: A Song Of Ice And Fire / Gendrya
Series: Gendrya Week (3/?)
Words: 9,575
Chapter(s): 1/7
Rating: Teen+
AO3 / / FF.net

“So,” Arya declares as she signs her name at the bottom of the contract. She finishes off the final k with a flourish, a swooping curve that loops once and underlines the preceding letters of her name. “We’re in agreement.”

Gendry nervously takes the pen from her and signs his own name, a shaky and unsure signature that differs so incredibly from hers. “We are. I look forward to fake dating you until this wedding business is through.”

Arya grins at him, and she feels a twinge of pride at seeing him gulp at the flash of her teeth. “That’s what you think.”

summary: Look i adore the theory that Arya gets Robb’s crown from Stoneheart and uses it to crown Bran and/or Rickon. Even though i know...
body:
Look i adore the theory that Arya gets Robb’s crown from Stoneheart and uses it to crown Bran and/or Rickon. Even though i know it wont happen or even makes a lot of sense logistically i wish that Arya could meet up with Jeyne Westerling. 

Because i think about this a bit to often:

“The girl turned her head away. “It is nothing,” insisted her mother, a stern-faced woman in a gown of green velvet. A necklace of golden seashells looped about her long, thin neck. “She would not give up the little crown the rebel gave her, and when I tried to take it from her head the willful child fought me.”

“It was mine.” Jeyne sobbed. “You had no right. Robb had it made for me. I loved him.” - Jaime VII, AFfC 

They took the crown Robb gave her and personally i kind of would like to see where Arya gets to meet the woman who her brother loved enough to die for and who loved him in return  and offer her a bit of comfort in the only thing they have left of Robb. 

Again unlikely, but i still like the idea.
